00:41:14,477 --> 00:41:36,736
I just wanted to share I've been collecting some input about this question and I am thinking back to how we crafted the policy around the calendar creation originally and we were indeed trying to reflect a more inclusive community and a place of belonging even though we weren't using the word belong at that time, right?

407
00:41:36,756 --> 00:41:40,119
I think that was part of the goal and I think we knew

408
00:41:40,819 --> 00:41:48,723
that there would be times in the decades where this kind of calendar would become a problem.

409
00:41:49,684 --> 00:41:54,726
We brought it forward just like we would have expected or anticipated when we wrote that policy.

410
00:41:54,746 --> 00:42:09,954
I think what is unique about next year is that in order to fulfill our policy fully, which would include observance of Good Friday and Eid al-Adha,

411
00:42:10,934 --> 00:42:12,315
Rosh Hashanah falls on a weekend.

412
00:42:12,875 --> 00:42:15,316
So we would need two additional days.

413
00:42:15,596 --> 00:42:34,824
So one day certainly is important operationally to address Good Friday and the staff absences that came with that day because as you mentioned like our staff the makeup of our staff is not exactly the same as sort of the the broader community.

414
00:42:36,910 --> 00:42:44,892
But if we could find two more days, we could carry out our full objective of our calendar under our policy.

415
00:42:46,452 --> 00:43:04,277
As far as I can tell, the only day that the school committee could act on alone would be to not observe Juneteenth on the 18th, which is not Juneteenth, that's the 19th, when

416
00:43:06,737 --> 00:43:14,002
In the state of Massachusetts, when a holiday falls on a Saturday, it is not required to be observed on a Friday.

417
00:43:14,042 --> 00:43:24,730
In fact, under the Secretary of State, when a holiday falls on a Saturday, organizations are to remain open both Friday and Monday and sort of split time.

418
00:43:24,830 --> 00:43:30,815
So we could possibly do something there, although I don't think that necessarily promotes belonging.

419
00:43:31,669 --> 00:43:31,949
either.

420
00:43:33,590 --> 00:43:40,995
So that to me is the only thing that I can see that this body could do without some sort of broader collaboration.

421
00:43:43,096 --> 00:43:54,363
And I think you know I don't I guess and that's sort of a conversation for this group but I don't think we're saying we want to abandon the practices that we have set up.

422
00:43:54,903 --> 00:44:00,026
I think what we're saying is we have to work together somehow some way to get through

423
00:44:00,731 --> 00:44:10,238
this particular year of the calendar because of the way all of these holidays fall and Labor Day starts late and you know and on and on and on.

424
00:44:11,019 --> 00:44:24,950
I think there are other options that were suggested to me by various members of the of the community that would be appealing to them all of which would require like collaboration from from our teachers union in particular because their contract has

425
00:44:25,595 --> 00:44:31,877
specific stipulations in it about how the school calendar falls in some cases.

426
00:44:32,517 --> 00:44:42,561
And those days that people have suggested to me, and I just wanna make sure that publicly we are talking about them, is the Friday before Labor Day becoming a school day.

427
00:44:42,601 --> 00:44:54,185
And so that Good Friday could be a full day off, albeit that does not solve the two calendar day problem if we are trying to be as inclusive as our policy sets forward.

428
00:44:55,869 --> 00:45:10,058
The other suggestions that I have heard is swap an early release day on the 23rd of December with Good Friday so that students would be in school for a full day on the 23rd, which is not a holy day.

429
00:45:10,078 --> 00:45:12,199
It is not even the day before a holy day.

430
00:45:12,520 --> 00:45:19,764
The holy day is two days later for Good Friday, although operationally I think there's still a question about whether that would

431
00:45:21,536 --> 00:45:22,576
be workable or not.

432
00:45:24,577 --> 00:45:31,298
And then the other suggestion that lots of parents have this year in particular because of the late start of school was simply to start school earlier.

433
00:45:32,118 --> 00:45:43,761
And they're particularly our youngest students are having, the parents of our youngest students have lots and lots of child care issues at the end of August this year because of the way the calendar is falling so late.

434
00:45:44,281 --> 00:45:48,042
Other districts have made decisions to go back sooner than their contract allows.

435
00:45:48,142 --> 00:45:50,863
So those are the things that sort of people have.

436
00:45:51,723 --> 00:45:52,904
